column1: #FORMAT=WebAnno TSV 3.2
#Text=[0517] Preparation of Non-standard Reagents and Synthetic Intermediates Utilized in the Examples
#Text=[0518] Preparation A1: Synthesis of Benzyloxycarbonylamino-7-oxo-6-aza-bic-yclo[3.2.1]octane-6-carboxylic acid tert-butyl ester
#Text=[0519] Preparation A1, Step 1: (1S,2R)-cis-2-Methoxycarbonyl-cyclohex-4-en-e-1-carboxylic acid (66.0 g, see Bolm et al.
#Text=J.
#Text=Org.
#Text=Chem. 2000, 65, 6984-6991) was dissolved in dry acetone (815 mL) prior to the addition of triethylamine (43.4 g).
#Text=This solution was cooled to 0.degree.
#Text=C. and ethyl chloroformate (46.7 g) was added.
#Text=The resulting solution was stirred 1 h before NaN.sub.3 (35.0 g) was added.
#Text=The cooling bath was removed, and the reaction was warmed to rt overnight.
#Text=All solid material was removed by filtration, and the solution was partially concentrated.
#Text=Water was slowly added and the organic layer was separated.
#Text=The aqueous layer was extracted with ether.
#Text=The combined organic layers were washed with water and brine before they were dried, filtered, and concentrated.
#Text=The resulting oil (66.1 g) was dissolved in benzene (800 mL) and was warmed to a gentle reflux.
#Text=After 4 h, the solution was cooled back to rt.
#Text=Benzyl alcohol (37.5 g) and p-TsOH (1.5 g) were added, and the solution was warmed back to a gentle reflux overnight.

#Text=After cooling to rt, the reaction was washed with NaHCO.sub.3 and brine, dried, filtered, and concentrated to give (1R,6S)-6-benzyloxycarbonylamino-cyclohex-3-enecarbo-xylic acid methyl ester (97.7 g).
#Text=MS found: (M+H).sup.+=290.2.

#Text=[0520] Preparation A1, Step 2: A sample of (1R,6S)-6-benzyloxycarbonylamin-o-cyclohex-3-enecarboxylic acid methyl ester (91.4 g) was dissolved in MeOH (500 mL) prior to the dropwise addition of NaOH (25.3 g) in water (95 mL).
#Text=After 3 h, the solution was partially concentrated and an Et.sub.2O/water mixture was added.
#Text=The aqueous layer was separated and was acidified (pH.about.2) with concentrated HCl.
#Text=The resulting mixture was extracted with EtOAc.
#Text=The combined organic layers were washed with water and brine before they were dried, filtered, and concentrated to give (1R,6S)-6-benzyloxycarbonylamino-cyclohex-3-enecarboxylic acid (72.7 g).
#Text=MS found: (M+H).sup.+=276.2.

#Text=[0521] Preparation A1, Step 3: A sample of (1R,6S)-6-benzyloxycarbonylamin-o-cyclohex-3-enecarboxylic acid (72 g) was dissolved in CH.sub.2Cl.sub.2 (750 mL) prior to the addition of CDI (50.9 g).
#Text=After 2.5 h water was added, and the solution was extracted with CH.sub.2Cl.sub.2.
#Text=The combined organic layers were dried, filtered, and concentrated.
#Text=The resulting material was dissolved in CH.sub.2Cl.sub.2 and ammonia gas was bubbled through the solution for 1.5 h.
#Text=After stirring overnight, the majority of the solvent was removed and Et.sub.2O was added.
#Text=The product precipitated as a white solid and was collected to give (1R,6S)-6-carbamoyl-cyclohex-3--enyl)-carbamic acid benzyl ester (61.5 g).
#Text=MS found: (M+H).sup.+=275.3.
